# .trivyignore — accepted-risk CVEs with rationale.
#
# Each entry must include WHY this CVE is not exploitable in this app's
# context. Re-evaluate periodically. Remove the suppression as soon as
# the underlying issue is fixed upstream.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2024-24790 — Go stdlib net/netip: IPv4-mapped IPv6 address handling
# CVE-2025-68121 — Go stdlib crypto/tls: TLS session resumption certificate
#                  validation
#
# Both flagged in:
#   - app/node_modules/@esbuild/linux-x64/bin/esbuild
#   - app/node_modules/@esbuild-kit/core-utils/node_modules/esbuild/bin/esbuild
#
# These are the Go-built esbuild binaries shipped by the esbuild npm package.
# esbuild is a devDependency used at build time only. The runtime entrypoint
# is `bun serve.js` → `bun build/index.js`, which is the SvelteKit production
# server output; it never spawns or imports esbuild. The Go stdlib code paths
# that contain these CVEs (net/netip TLS session resumption) are unreachable
# at runtime — esbuild is not running, not listening on a port, and not
# accepting connections.
#
# Long-term fix: the runtime stage of the Containerfile should not ship
# devDependencies. That requires moving @sveltejs/kit (and any of its
# transitive runtime requirements) from devDependencies to dependencies so
# that `bun install --production` keeps a working tree. Tracked as a
# follow-up; in the meantime these suppressions document the reasoning.
#
# Re-evaluate when:
#   - esbuild ships a release rebuilt with Go ≥ 1.24.13 / 1.25.7 / 1.26.0-rc.3
#   - Or the Containerfile is restructured to install --production at runtime
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2025-68121
